author: Kiniravu Karomanu
notes: I wrote the words down in their most accurate pronounciation form.
classification: Austronesian, Malayo-Polynesian, Central-Eastern Malayo-Polynesian, Eastern Malayo-Polynesian, Oceanic, Western Oceanic, Papuan Tip, Peripheral, Central Papuan, Sinagoro-Keapara

author: back
glottocode: lower back including hips, although there is another word sprcifically for hips, which is \kepo\"."

author: man/male
glottocode: 1)tau as in man, male. 2)tau as in one(person) one as in \the evil/bad one(tau tsikana)\"
notes: \"the one who fights in a war/ a warrior(vetali tauna)\"
problems: or in \"the one who teaches/informs(veve?aripa tauna)\" etc.."

author: man/male
glottocode: maru is commonly used to refer to man or male

author: to shoot
glottocode: piti - to shoot(general term, does not include arrows)

author: to hit
glottocode: to hit with the hand only/bare hand

author: to hit
glottocode: kwari - to hit with an object

author: to split
glottocode: qavaluga - to break open into pieces or parts or halves

author: to fly
glottocode: \rau\" is more of a bird flying while flapping its wings while lovo is more like gliding and soaring without flapping wings"

author: black
glottocode: (black, also used to describe dark/darker shade of a colour)

author: red
glottocode: kalovakalova - from the word for fire which is \kalova(qalova)\". It does not strictly describe red but a color spectrum of fire from red to orange(excluding yellow)."

author: wide
glottocode: wide and flat, or just flat surface
